{{en-noun}}

# A group of people, especially within a political organization, which expresses a [[shared]] [[belief]] or [[opinion]] different from people who are not part of the group.
#* {{quote-book|title=Essays, Moral and Political|author=[[w:David Hume|David Hume]]|year=1748|chapter=Of Parties in General — How '''factions''' arise and contend.|passage=Real '''factions''' may be divided into those from interest, from principle, and from affection}}
